&gt;&gt; Thank you Julian.

00:20:48.436 --> 00:20:48.976 A:middle
Hello everyone.

00:20:53.046 --> 00:20:56.976 A:middle
Now we can make this quick and

00:20:57.526 --> 00:20:59.646 A:middle
add a simple click sound to this

00:20:59.646 --> 00:21:00.046 A:middle
button.


00:20:59.646 --> 00:21:00.046 A:middle
button.

00:21:00.666 --> 00:21:04.576 A:middle
Sounds pretty good or could it

00:21:04.576 --> 00:21:05.656 A:middle
be better?

00:21:06.416 --> 00:21:07.866 A:middle
Could Julian have done a better

00:21:07.866 --> 00:21:09.196 A:middle
job and invited me a little

00:21:09.196 --> 00:21:10.976 A:middle
earlier on in the process?

00:21:15.046 --> 00:21:15.586 A:middle
I'd like to tell you a few

00:21:15.586 --> 00:21:16.906 A:middle
things about how as I a sound

00:21:16.906 --> 00:21:18.316 A:middle
designer could approach a

00:21:18.316 --> 00:21:19.256 A:middle
project like this.

00:21:19.736 --> 00:21:23.066 A:middle
I'll talk about where to look

00:21:23.066 --> 00:21:25.696 A:middle
for inspiration, about designing

00:21:25.696 --> 00:21:28.456 A:middle
the sound, and some key building

00:21:28.456 --> 00:21:30.186 A:middle
blocks that we use while doing

00:21:30.186 --> 00:21:30.466 A:middle
this.

00:21:32.376 --> 00:21:34.576 A:middle
But before we dive in why do we

00:21:34.576 --> 00:21:35.466 A:middle
talk about sound?

00:21:35.986 --> 00:21:39.536 A:middle
Now some of you may think our

00:21:39.536 --> 00:21:41.716 A:middle
users mute the sound on their

00:21:41.716 --> 00:21:44.296 A:middle
phone quite often, is it

00:21:44.676 --> 00:21:46.936 A:middle
important to add sound to my

00:21:47.226 --> 00:21:47.786 A:middle
app?

00:21:48.636 --> 00:21:50.056 A:middle
Well of course it's up to you

00:21:50.056 --> 00:21:52.296 A:middle
but George Lucas has said that

00:21:52.296 --> 00:21:54.846 A:middle
50% of the experience of a movie

00:21:54.846 --> 00:21:56.656 A:middle
is determined by what we hear,

00:21:57.276 --> 00:21:59.406 A:middle
by its music and sound design.


00:22:00.516 --> 00:22:02.736 A:middle
And sound is all around us, we

00:22:02.736 --> 00:22:05.046 A:middle
use it to navigate through the

00:22:05.046 --> 00:22:05.456 A:middle
world.

00:22:07.156 --> 00:22:10.636 A:middle
And sound can help enrich the

00:22:10.636 --> 00:22:12.506 A:middle
experience of your products.

00:22:13.056 --> 00:22:16.506 A:middle
And it helps us remember the

00:22:16.506 --> 00:22:19.026 A:middle
experiences of your app, as well

00:22:19.026 --> 00:22:22.976 A:middle
as your brand, so it can have a

00:22:22.976 --> 00:22:24.226 A:middle
big impact.

00:22:25.516 --> 00:22:26.676 A:middle
So where do we look for

00:22:26.676 --> 00:22:27.876 A:middle
inspiration when we want to

00:22:27.876 --> 00:22:29.656 A:middle
design sound for a button?

00:22:30.366 --> 00:22:32.046 A:middle
Well we can start by taking a

00:22:32.046 --> 00:22:33.396 A:middle
little detour and looking at

00:22:34.086 --> 00:22:35.816 A:middle
some real-world buttons.

00:22:37.076 --> 00:22:40.416 A:middle
Some of them are made of cheap

00:22:40.686 --> 00:22:42.976 A:middle
materials and sound like this,

00:22:43.726 --> 00:22:45.416 A:middle
while others are made of high

00:22:45.416 --> 00:22:47.116 A:middle
quality materials and sound like

00:22:47.796 --> 00:22:47.986 A:middle
this.

00:22:48.896 --> 00:22:49.996 A:middle
Well this was actually a

00:22:50.356 --> 00:22:52.436 A:middle
recording of the volume button

00:22:52.486 --> 00:22:54.606 A:middle
on an iPhone X, of course we

00:22:54.606 --> 00:22:56.306 A:middle
amplified it quite a bit.

00:22:58.576 --> 00:23:00.316 A:middle
These sounds though are


00:22:58.576 --> 00:23:00.316 A:middle
These sounds though are

00:23:00.316 --> 00:23:02.546 A:middle
essentially byproducts, they're

00:23:02.546 --> 00:23:05.156 A:middle
not necessarily designed they're

00:23:05.156 --> 00:23:06.746 A:middle
defined by the materials these

00:23:06.746 --> 00:23:07.966 A:middle
buttons are made of.

00:23:09.326 --> 00:23:10.766 A:middle
But because we're designed for

00:23:10.766 --> 00:23:11.726 A:middle
software we have a lot of

00:23:11.726 --> 00:23:15.846 A:middle
freedom, so we can choose to not

00:23:15.886 --> 00:23:18.016 A:middle
play any sounds at all and often

00:23:18.016 --> 00:23:18.926 A:middle
that is what we do.

00:23:19.466 --> 00:23:23.566 A:middle
But if we do decide it's useful

00:23:23.566 --> 00:23:27.026 A:middle
to add sounds to UI elements

00:23:27.806 --> 00:23:29.126 A:middle
then we can take cues from

00:23:29.126 --> 00:23:31.666 A:middle
real-world analogs to add

00:23:31.696 --> 00:23:34.166 A:middle
meaning to these UI sounds and

00:23:34.726 --> 00:23:36.106 A:middle
to help our users understand

00:23:39.236 --> 00:23:39.396 A:middle
them.

00:23:39.546 --> 00:23:40.876 A:middle
Now do you want to add sound to

00:23:40.876 --> 00:23:41.246 A:middle
your app?

00:23:41.246 --> 00:23:44.086 A:middle
Well it depends, think about

00:23:44.086 --> 00:23:46.456 A:middle
category your app falls in, who

00:23:46.536 --> 00:23:48.226 A:middle
will use the app and what will

00:23:48.226 --> 00:23:51.586 A:middle
their expectations be, and what

00:23:51.586 --> 00:23:52.836 A:middle
is the context, where will the

00:23:52.836 --> 00:23:53.716 A:middle
app be used.

00:23:54.456 --> 00:23:57.386 A:middle
For our app we know it will be

00:23:57.386 --> 00:23:59.256 A:middle
used by people who like to eat

00:23:59.296 --> 00:24:01.676 A:middle
toast and they're used to making


00:23:59.296 --> 00:24:01.676 A:middle
toast and they're used to making

00:24:01.676 --> 00:24:03.996 A:middle
toast in the kitchen, but from

00:24:03.996 --> 00:24:05.186 A:middle
now on they can make it from

00:24:05.186 --> 00:24:07.686 A:middle
anywhere in the house.

00:24:07.886 --> 00:24:10.026 A:middle
They can still though use the

00:24:10.026 --> 00:24:11.546 A:middle
audible cues they're used to

00:24:11.546 --> 00:24:12.656 A:middle
getting from their toaster in

00:24:12.656 --> 00:24:14.756 A:middle
the kitchen, so for that reason

00:24:15.116 --> 00:24:17.286 A:middle
we think that this app is a

00:24:17.286 --> 00:24:19.416 A:middle
perfect candidate for the use of

00:24:20.876 --> 00:24:21.066 A:middle
sound.

00:24:21.216 --> 00:24:24.296 A:middle
So let's look at the process of

00:24:24.296 --> 00:24:27.206 A:middle
making toast and listen to

00:24:27.206 --> 00:24:28.346 A:middle
sounds we encounter.

00:24:30.316 --> 00:24:32.396 A:middle
Let's define if these sounds are

00:24:32.396 --> 00:24:35.046 A:middle
useful and if they are if we

00:24:35.046 --> 00:24:36.386 A:middle
want to use them in our design.

00:24:36.466 --> 00:24:39.366 A:middle
So we'll use Julian's timeline

00:24:39.366 --> 00:24:41.786 A:middle
for this and listen to the

00:24:41.786 --> 00:24:43.576 A:middle
sounds that this toaster makes.

00:24:44.856 --> 00:24:47.396 A:middle
First, we pull down the lever

00:24:48.406 --> 00:24:51.336 A:middle
and then we press it in place.

00:24:53.596 --> 00:24:55.516 A:middle
Now what we hear then is the

00:24:55.746 --> 00:24:57.286 A:middle
toaster heating up with a subtle

00:24:57.286 --> 00:24:58.736 A:middle
buzzing sound of the coil.

